Four Nigerian men were arrested in Cambodia on Tuesday, 2 March, for alleged online fraud and kidnapping. Deputy Prosecutor Seng Heang and his team in collaboration with the Ministry of Interior searched a condominium ( Zong Ruby) in Sen Sok district, Phnom Penh at 12:20 and arrested the Nigerian nationals. The four men were wanted in connection with a case of kidnapping in Vietnam and have been referred to the Criminal Police Department for further proceedings. Police confiscated 3 passports, 4 laptops, 8 cell phones, one SIM card Number, one yellow metal cord, 15,000 riel and US $ 5, and two bags. Source